HEADWORD: Gymnosperm
<hw>Gym"no*sperm</hw> <pr>(j⟦icr⟧m"n⟦osl⟧*sp⟦etil⟧rm)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant that bears naked seeds
(<it>i. e.</it>, seeds not inclosed in an ovary), as the common pine and
hemlock. Cf. <er>Angiosperm</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gymnospermous</ent>⟦br⟧
